</div>Given my state's financial situation, I am soooo glad that they didn't get these Olympics. That said, the Chicago bid had half the facilities and all of the hotels and most the infrastructure already built. It stood a much greater chance of actually making a profit. But, given the master fuck-up that is <STRIKE>FIFA</STRIKE> the IOC (like there's a difference), I can only hope this bankrupts the organization. I have so little interest in even watching most of the Olympics anymore.<br />
<br />
BTW: I met a parent whose daughter was in Rio for the under 16 world championships. She was saying that kids would come out of the water and their skin would be red with rashes. Athletes having to drop out of the race due to illness was rampant. Basically, every team had members get violently ill after swimming in that water. Honestly, I wish the individual countries would threaten to not go and have their own races some place else if they don't move the swim competition. I guess there is a place about a 100 miles north that does not have the same pollution issues that Rio does. As it stands, I can already see the memes that will come out of the three medal winners puking all over the podium as the national anthem of the winner is played.
						</blockquote>
